{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "We need to provision a two-site L3 VPN for customer 4555. Service name: 'VPRN-6297-CoreLink'. Site A at 192.168.73.192: svc-id 6297, RD 65104:6297, VRF CoreLink-VRF-Import/CoreLink-VRF-Export, interfaces: Lambda-Cluster-Master on port 1/1/c8/2 with IP 100.101.176.193/30; Lambda-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Broadcom11-4x10GE with IP 10.110.202.211/24; Lambda-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/1/c10/4 with IP 10.211.196.184/31. Site B at 192.168.13.106: svc-id 6297, RD 65210:6297, VRF CoreLink-VRF-Import/CoreLink-VRF-Export, interfaces: Mars-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c2/2 with IP 10.168.112.154/30; Mars-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Cisco10-4x25GE with IP 172.16.58.103/24; Mars-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 2/1/c8/4 with IP 10.99.115.60/31."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-6297-CoreLink\",\n    \"customer-id\": 4555,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-6297-CoreLink\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.73.192\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 6297,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65104:6297\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"CoreLink-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"CoreLink-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Lambda-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap